    "description": "CAC Holdings Corporation, through its subsidiaries, provides information technology services in Japan and internationally. It operates in two segments, IT and Overseas IT. The company constructs and operates information systems. It also offers systems development, integration, operation, management, consulting, and maintenance, as well as BPO/BTO services; develops and sells packaged software; and plans, develops, and sells production management systems. In addition, the company engages in the development of machine learning, artificial intelligence, and application, as well as new business; aquaculture using IoT and AI; development of mobile telecommunications products and communication systems, as well as registered telecommunications services; financial services and IT consulting; BPO services for waste management; help desk services; and software development. Further, it is involved in engineering and research and development services, outsourced product development, IT infrastructure management, managed services, and enterprise applications for banking, telecom, and manufacturing industries; and sale and maintenance of software products. The company was formerly known as CAC Corporation and changed its name to CAC Holdings Corporation in April 2014. CAC Holdings Corporation was founded in 1966 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
